I would start by using a rag and mineral spirits to remove old wax.
Then examine the top for scratches and other disfigurements. Realize
that you will not remove all the marks. Next you an use mineral
spirits and #0000 steel wool to abrade the top layer of finish off
then use a buffer and fine polishing compound. Or, skip the wool and
go right to the buffing stage. Lastly use a paste wax.

Chances are that is all you will have to do.

