putting linseed oil over an original finish is not a good practice.
linseed oil crosslinks and becomes impossible to remove without
damaging the underlying coating. in addition, it will darken over
time. true, it was used in the past, only because it was cheap and
readily available.

when french polishing, which is what was described here, oil is used
only to lubricate the pad and should be removed before the next
coating.

